### Harsha

**Maharajadhiraja**
*Sakalottarapathanātha*
*Śilāditya*
*Paramabhattāraka*
*Parama-Maheśwara*
*Gaudeśwara* &#91;1&#93;

A coin of Harshavardhana, dated to his reign, c. 606–647 CE. A small metal disc to represent a life's work. &#91;2&#93;

**Maharajadhiraja of Kannauj**
**Reign:** April 606 – 647
**Predecessor:** [Rajyavardhana](/Rajyavardhana) (as the less ambitious King of Thanesar)
**Successor:** [Arunāsva](/Arun%C4%81sva) (as King of Kannauj, a title he didn't hold for long)

**Born:** 4 June 590 &#91;3&#93;
Possibly in Sthanvishvara, [Kingdom of Thanesar](/Pushyabhuti_dynasty) (a place now known as [Thanesar](/Thanesar), [Haryana](/Haryana), [India](/India)) &#91;4&#93; &#91;5&#93;
